name: inorganic phosphorus, as P2O5 to generic market for organo-mineral phosphorus, as P2O5 | organo-mineral phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5 | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/23440/documentation

This is a renaming activity that connects "inorganic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5" with "organo-mineral phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5". It is assumed that in the shortage of "organo-mineral phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5", a consumer of it will turn its consumption pattern and use an "inorganic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5". In theory, the "inorganic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5" can substitute the "organo-mineral phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5" in an equal mass ratio, considering only the nutrient content.;This dataset is meant to be employed only in the consequential system model where it is assumed that inorganic can replace organic fertiliser. The production volume of this activity is set to zero so it does not react with attributional supply chains.

The activity starts with the reception of inorganic phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5.

The activity ends with organo-mineral phosphorus fertiliser, as P2O5 being ready for transportation.
category: A:Agriculture, forestry and fishing/01:Crop and animal production, hunting and related service activities/016:Support activities to agriculture and post-harvest crop activities/0161:Support activities for crop production

processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Inventory is based on the nutrient content of the fertiliser.
